        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 16 at 4:37PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 430 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking large area of moderate
snowfall affecting areas around Brady, Choteau, Conrad, Shelby and
Inverness, which was moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Moderate snowfall, with visibility below a half mile.

SOURCE...Radar and web camera indicated.

IMPACT...Poor driving visibility, and slush snow accumulations on
roadways and bridges.

Locations impacted include...
Dupuyer, Marias Pass, Oilmont, Rudyard, Pishkun Reservoir, Tiber
Dam, Joplin, Brady, Santa Rita, Conrad, Saint Mary, Heart Butte,
Simpson, Dutton, Augusta, East Glacier Park Village, and Inverness.
</description>
        <instruction>Reduce driving speeds in areas of poor visibility.</instruction>
